145
00:11:43,868 --> 00:11:45,536
It's a fucking dog.

146
00:11:46,454 --> 00:11:47,788
You're a stony little bastard.

147
00:11:47,872 --> 00:11:50,582
I'm what time and circumstance
have made me.

148
00:11:52,168 --> 00:11:53,544
Your mother keeps me informed.

149
00:11:53,628 --> 00:11:55,379
Those must be pleasant conversations.

150
00:11:56,673 --> 00:12:00,676
You have no concept of the ways
that people can be close.

151
00:12:02,178 --> 00:12:05,139
I have a pretty good idea.
You were 54. She was 13.

152
00:12:08,518 --> 00:12:09,893
You'd have done the same thing.

153
00:12:10,311 --> 00:12:11,437
You don't know me very well.

154
00:12:11,521 --> 00:12:14,523
Oh, I know you backwards and forwards.

155
00:12:15,859 --> 00:12:18,152
You want anything
you can lay your hands on,

156
00:12:18,736 --> 00:12:21,155
and nothing's gonna stop you from getting it.

157
00:12:22,991 --> 00:12:25,701
I expect nothing less from my son, though.

158
00:12:30,832 --> 00:12:32,124
This reunion over?

159
00:12:34,169 --> 00:12:35,210
I'm dying, boy.

160
00:12:39,382 --> 00:12:41,925
Well, then I will call you a priest.

161
00:12:42,010 --> 00:12:45,053
You know what this town was
before I came here?

162
00:12:48,558 --> 00:12:49,892
A fucking swamp.

163
00:12:50,810 --> 00:12:54,146
Sand blowing through
shitty boarding houses.

164
00:12:55,064 --> 00:12:56,231
Nobody wanted to come here.

165
00:12:58,026 --> 00:12:59,401
But I drained that swamp.

166
00:13:00,904 --> 00:13:04,406
I paved those streets. I put up those hotels.

167
00:13:06,743 --> 00:13:08,702
I made this fucking city.

168
00:13:09,454 --> 00:13:11,747
You and your giant blue ox, right?

169
00:13:11,998 --> 00:13:13,373
Don't sass me, boy.

170
00:13:15,919 --> 00:13:17,336
I'm just trying to tell you something.

171
00:13:17,462 --> 00:13:20,255
What are you trying to tell me?

172
00:13:24,010 --> 00:13:26,136
The wrong man is running this town.

173
00:13:35,438 --> 00:13:37,940
- Where are you going?
- I don't feel well.

174
00:14:07,011 --> 00:14:10,055
He knows I'm unhappy,
but he'd never dream I'd leave.

175
00:14:10,139 --> 00:14:12,099
Neither would Robert.

176
00:14:12,642 --> 00:14:15,227
Pack lightly.
One suitcase for you and Tommy both.

177
00:14:15,478 --> 00:14:17,896
We can buy whatever we need
once we're abroad.

178
00:14:17,981 --> 00:14:19,565
I'd like a fresh start anyway.

179
00:14:21,484 --> 00:14:23,902
The man from Cunard says
we're to be at the dock an hour early.

180
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:25,696
We'll meet here, and then go to...

181
00:14:25,780 --> 00:14:27,155
God damn it!

182
00:14:28,491 --> 00:14:29,533
Dearest?

183
00:14:30,577 --> 00:14:31,618
Hello?

184
00:14:33,705 --> 00:14:35,747
I'm helpless on these damned things.

185
00:14:36,499 --> 00:14:38,333
I spilled developer on my trousers.

186
00:14:38,626 --> 00:14:40,627
- It's all over the floor.
- I'll get it later. Sit.

187
00:14:54,851 --> 00:14:56,602
I'll see you later, Mary.

188
00:15:04,986 --> 00:15:06,612
What were you two conspiring about?

189
00:15:07,864 --> 00:15:08,947
What?

190
00:15:09,824 --> 00:15:11,491
I heard hushed voices.

191
00:15:12,076 --> 00:15:13,702
Oh. Just girl talk.

192
00:15:14,996 --> 00:15:17,706
Well, you do like your little games, don't you?

193
00:15:19,459 --> 00:15:20,792
You seem to enjoy them yourself.

194
00:15:21,919 --> 00:15:23,545
Very wicked, my love.

195
00:15:39,562 --> 00:15:40,896
Where are you calling from?

196
00:15:40,980 --> 00:15:42,064
The lobby.

197
00:15:42,398 --> 00:15:44,107
Are you out of your fucking mind?

198
00:15:44,567 --> 00:15:46,902
I couldn't call from the post office.
It wasn't safe.

199
00:15:47,028 --> 00:15:48,570
You were cleared, weren't you?

200
00:15:48,946 --> 00:15:50,405
There's nothing he can do.

201
00:15:50,573 --> 00:15:52,074
He's not letting go of this.

202
00:15:52,408 --> 00:15:54,701
Then give him something he can't argue with.

203
00:15:54,786 --> 00:15:55,869
Like what?

204
00:15:58,331 --> 00:15:59,831
You're a Prohi, aren't you?

205
00:15:59,916 --> 00:16:02,250
- Go find bootleggers.
- Any suggestions?

206
00:16:04,003 --> 00:16:07,005
Head out toward Mays Landing,
along the Black Horse.

207
00:16:07,340 --> 00:16:11,093
I wouldn't be surprised if there was
a major illegal distillery operating there.

208
00:16:11,260 --> 00:16:12,219
How far?

209
00:16:12,303 --> 00:16:13,720
You want me to make the arrest, too?

210
00:16:14,597 --> 00:16:17,432
Just past mile marker 14, on the left.

211
00:16:18,893 --> 00:16:20,060
Don't get spooked, kid.

212
00:16:20,770 --> 00:16:21,728
No, sir.

213
00:16:21,813 --> 00:16:24,940
Now go look like a hero,
and let's not talk again.

214
00:16:33,658 --> 00:16:35,033
Yes, you're standing there.

215
00:16:37,537 --> 00:16:39,287
A lady in distress.

216
00:16:40,748 --> 00:16:41,915
That son of a bitch.

217
00:16:42,166 --> 00:16:45,293
Annabelle, you can tell me whatever you want,

218
00:16:45,378 --> 00:16:48,547
but don't scream, don't cry
and don't throw anything.

219
00:16:56,514 --> 00:16:59,141
I had money under the floorboards.

220
00:17:00,017 --> 00:17:01,435
Harry took it all.

221
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:03,270
How much?

222
00:17:03,479 --> 00:17:05,939
$3,682.

223
00:17:08,651 --> 00:17:09,818
I counted it every night.

224
00:17:10,653 --> 00:17:12,028
And you want me to have him arrested.

225
00:17:12,196 --> 00:17:13,488
I sure as hell do.

226
00:17:13,573 --> 00:17:15,824
To get back the money you lifted from him.

227
00:17:16,492 --> 00:17:18,285
I worked my tail off for it.

228
00:17:20,955 --> 00:17:22,497
My little girl.

229
00:17:25,501 --> 00:17:27,878
You said you wouldn't do this.

230
00:17:41,434 --> 00:17:43,059
This will see you through the summer.

231
00:17:45,688 --> 00:17:48,857
Come on, let's just skip to the part
where you say you'll do anything for me.

232
00:17:49,192 --> 00:17:50,400
Well, I would.

233
00:17:52,403 --> 00:17:54,029
Draw the curtains, and I'll do it right now.

234
00:17:55,281 --> 00:17:56,740
What happened to the tears?

235
00:17:58,201 --> 00:18:00,827
Ride me like you used to
and I'll soak the pillow through.

236
00:18:03,164 --> 00:18:05,373
I'll keep that one in my pocket.

237
00:18:06,793 --> 00:18:08,210
And he will, you know.

238
00:18:12,048 --> 00:18:15,884
Mr. Thompson's gift is
to never forget who owes him what.

239
00:18:16,803 --> 00:18:18,303
It's generally a good principle.

240
00:18:19,972 --> 00:18:21,890
Harry found her stash and did a bunk.

241
00:18:21,974 --> 00:18:22,974
I know.

242
00:18:23,559 --> 00:18:26,645
Did you mention
I already gave you $50 myself?

243
00:18:27,313 --> 00:18:29,064
I guess we're both a soft touch.

244
00:18:35,446 --> 00:18:37,739
Thanks for helping a girl out.

245
00:18:45,915 --> 00:18:47,541
I thought you might like to hear,

246
00:18:47,834 --> 00:18:51,336
the League of Women Voters
is going to formally endorse Mr. Bader.

247
00:18:51,921 --> 00:18:55,090
- That's wonderful.
- Then I'm glad to have been of use to you.

248
00:19:04,934 --> 00:19:06,518
How did he look?

249
00:19:08,771 --> 00:19:10,647
Looks like he's dying.

250
00:19:11,774 --> 00:19:13,066
He smelled like garlic.

251
00:19:15,403 --> 00:19:18,405
He says you two see each other.

252
00:19:20,283 --> 00:19:22,284
We began keeping in touch.

253
00:19:23,286 --> 00:19:25,620
We have you in common, after all.

254
00:19:26,664 --> 00:19:30,292
When you enlisted, he called me.
He was very concerned.

255
00:19:32,253 --> 00:19:35,297
He lost his brother at the Battle of Vicksburg.

256
00:19:36,257 --> 00:19:37,591
Well, he needn't have worried.

257
00:19:38,217 --> 00:19:39,885
I told him you would come back.

258
00:19:42,305 --> 00:19:44,139
Lady Jean told me so.

259
00:19:44,682 --> 00:19:46,808
The fortune-teller? Ma, Jesus.

260
00:19:47,143 --> 00:19:48,643
She was right, wasn't she?

261
00:19:50,563 --> 00:19:51,980
There's rhubarb pie.

262
00:19:54,692 --> 00:19:56,568
You were 13 years old.

263
00:19:59,488 --> 00:20:02,115
You were by yourself, and you had me.

264
00:20:04,285 --> 00:20:06,328
I wasn't completely alone.

265
00:20:07,288 --> 00:20:09,831
Nucky Thompson was looking after us.

266
00:20:12,335 --> 00:20:14,044
And why was he doing that?

267
00:20:15,671 --> 00:20:17,422
He was the sheriff.

268
00:20:17,757 --> 00:20:20,091
He worked for your father and...

269
00:20:24,388 --> 00:20:25,555
You remember this?

270
00:20:31,187 --> 00:20:33,271
May Day, 1897.

271
00:20:34,857 --> 00:20:37,025
I was one of King Neptune's consorts.

272
00:20:41,197 --> 00:20:42,697
Your father saw me.

273
00:20:43,532 --> 00:20:47,243
And Nucky worked for him,
and later that day...

274
00:20:47,995 --> 00:20:49,579
Well, that night, really.

275
00:20:50,247 --> 00:20:51,873
Nucky brought me to him

276
00:20:53,292 --> 00:20:56,336
because that was one of the things
he did for the Commodore.

277
00:20:58,005 --> 00:21:01,132
And we proceeded in that fashion
for some time.

278
00:21:07,223 --> 00:21:08,431
A pimp.

279
00:21:11,894 --> 00:21:13,311
An ambitious young man

280
00:21:14,146 --> 00:21:15,480
who wanted to get ahead.

281
00:21:17,775 --> 00:21:18,900
He had a wife.

282
00:21:19,485 --> 00:21:21,361
He wanted to start a family.

283
00:21:21,445 --> 00:21:22,946
And that makes it okay?

284
00:21:23,781 --> 00:21:25,532
You remember Mabel?

285
00:21:26,659 --> 00:21:27,993
She was a lovely woman.

286
00:21:29,161 --> 00:21:30,578
It's a tragedy.

287
00:21:34,458 --> 00:21:37,377
Nucky has been kind in his way

288
00:21:38,963 --> 00:21:40,588
to you and me both.

289
00:21:43,050 --> 00:21:47,220
I suppose the whole affair
has always bothered him.

290
00:21:51,142 --> 00:21:52,934
Do you remember how long this used to be?

291
00:21:54,812 --> 00:21:55,812
Mmm.

292
00:22:01,068 --> 00:22:03,987
I told the doctor that I'd meet him
at your father's house.

293
00:22:07,283 --> 00:22:09,492
No one deserves to die alone.

294
00:22:34,393 --> 00:22:37,103
That was the marker a little ways back.

295
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:38,938
It should be around here somewhere.

296
00:22:40,816 --> 00:22:42,817
And this anonymous source

297
00:22:43,486 --> 00:22:45,820
wouldn't have any reason to lie?

298
00:22:56,165 --> 00:22:57,415
You think maybe there's a...

299
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,833
Quiet.

300
00:23:29,365 --> 00:23:31,032
What are they doing here?

301
00:23:31,242 --> 00:23:33,409
Now we ain't doing nothing wrong here.

302
00:23:34,787 --> 00:23:35,787
Gentlemen.

303
00:23:37,206 --> 00:23:41,167
Special Agent Van Alden
with the Bureau of Internal Revenue.

304
00:23:43,629 --> 00:23:44,754
What's going on here?

305
00:23:45,339 --> 00:23:49,509
Just strengthening the Lord's army,
one lost soul at a time.

306
00:23:50,594 --> 00:23:53,012
I call it "the week of miracles."

307
00:23:54,181 --> 00:23:56,641
"And John did baptize in the wilderness."

308
00:23:58,352 --> 00:24:01,396
Deacon Cuffy,
Shiloh Baptist Church of Atlantic City.

309
00:24:02,314 --> 00:24:04,190
As far as I know, we are breaking no laws, sir.

310
00:24:04,275 --> 00:24:06,901
You think Christ hears you
in this forsaken place?

311
00:24:07,111 --> 00:24:08,903
Jesus is a wonder worker, sir.

312
00:24:09,238 --> 00:24:11,030
He hears everybody everywhere.

313
00:24:12,908 --> 00:24:14,659
- From the hollows to the hills.
- Yes, Lord.

314
00:24:14,827 --> 00:24:16,161
Just words, Deacon.

315
00:24:16,370 --> 00:24:18,329
No, sir. It's the gospel.

316
00:24:19,248 --> 00:24:20,748
And this gospel is truth.

317
00:24:21,458 --> 00:24:22,876
Turn from it however you may,

318
00:24:23,919 --> 00:24:26,087
but every road leads to a reckoning.

319
00:24:27,047 --> 00:24:28,381
That is what you believe?

320
00:24:28,507 --> 00:24:29,757
That's what I know.

321
00:24:30,426 --> 00:24:32,510
And I'll stake my place
in the kingdom upon it.

322
00:24:32,636 --> 00:24:34,053
- Oh, Lord.
- Praise Jesus.

323
00:24:34,138 --> 00:24:35,138
Yes, Lord.

324
00:24:35,431 --> 00:24:36,931
Then carry on.

325
00:24:40,436 --> 00:24:42,061
He that believeth

326
00:24:42,897 --> 00:24:44,439
and is baptized

327
00:24:45,274 --> 00:24:46,524
shall be saved.

328
00:24:46,650 --> 00:24:48,610
- Amen.
- Right now.

329
00:24:48,777 --> 00:24:50,987
But he that believeth not

330
00:24:51,906 --> 00:24:56,868
shall be condemned to the fires of damnation!

331
00:24:57,203 --> 00:24:58,786
Shouldn't we be looking for that still?

332
00:24:58,871 --> 00:25:01,789
Your people don't believe in heaven, do they?

333
00:25:02,082 --> 00:25:03,082
My people?

334
00:25:03,209 --> 00:25:05,710
Don't be glib. The Jews.

335
00:25:06,629 --> 00:25:08,671
No, not exactly.

336
00:25:09,089 --> 00:25:10,298
Rise up.

337
00:25:10,716 --> 00:25:12,300
Rise up, brothers and sisters.

338
00:25:12,384 --> 00:25:13,801
- Hallelujah.
- Hallelujah.

339
00:25:14,094 --> 00:25:16,054
Sir, I know you're under a lot of strain...

340
00:25:16,972 --> 00:25:20,308
But if you don't believe in heaven,
then how can you conceive of hell?

341
00:25:20,684 --> 00:25:22,977
- Surrender yourselves.
- Yes, yes.

342
00:25:23,270 --> 00:25:25,772
And rid yourselves of worldly sins.

343
00:25:25,898 --> 00:25:27,899
- Hallelujah.
- And be set free,

344
00:25:28,692 --> 00:25:30,068
unshackled,

345
00:25:31,612 --> 00:25:35,406
free to do the Lord's work.

346
00:25:35,741 --> 00:25:37,784
Amen. Amen.

347
00:25:37,868 --> 00:25:38,993
Amen.

348
00:25:39,578 --> 00:25:43,289
Let any man or woman with sin in their heart

349
00:25:43,832 --> 00:25:45,250
come forward

350
00:25:46,168 --> 00:25:52,257
to have that sin washed away
by the grace of Jesus Christ Almighty.

351
00:25:53,259 --> 00:25:56,761
- Jesus Christ.
- Yes, yes.

352
00:26:19,326 --> 00:26:20,368
Are you all right?

353
00:26:23,706 --> 00:26:24,831
I am.

354
00:26:25,499 --> 00:26:27,750
The question is, are you?

355
00:26:57,740 --> 00:26:59,073
Eat, dear.

356
00:27:00,075 --> 00:27:01,784
The angel of death.

357
00:27:04,079 --> 00:27:05,830
I knew you would be beautiful.

358
00:27:11,295 --> 00:27:13,087
He's quite jaundiced.

359
00:27:13,964 --> 00:27:15,506
Has he urinated?

360
00:27:15,591 --> 00:27:18,176
That chamber pot been empty for days.

361
00:27:18,635 --> 00:27:21,679
There's something wrong
with every organ in his body.

362
00:27:26,852 --> 00:27:29,771
- I'd like to run some tests.
- Is that really necessary?

363
00:27:30,606 --> 00:27:32,315
Just let me die, damn it.

364
00:27:32,900 --> 00:27:35,526
The Commodore don't like to be
fussed with, Doctor.

365
00:27:37,613 --> 00:27:40,281
I just need a hair sample.

366
00:27:41,867 --> 00:27:43,951
No. What are you doing?

367
00:27:44,036 --> 00:27:45,119
- It's all right.
- No.

368
00:27:45,204 --> 00:27:46,788
- Just a little piece of...
- No.

369
00:27:46,872 --> 00:27:48,539
- Look.
- It's okay.

370
00:27:48,624 --> 00:27:50,875
- No, he's trying to kill me.
- He's not trying to kill you, just...

371
00:27:50,959 --> 00:27:53,211
- He's trying to kill me.
- Relax. Relax.

372
00:27:53,295 --> 00:27:54,629
He's trying to help you.

373
00:27:54,797 --> 00:27:55,880
Easy.

374
00:27:58,926 --> 00:27:59,926
He's trying to help you.

375
00:28:00,010 --> 00:28:01,094
Yes.

376
00:28:03,305 --> 00:28:05,139
Okay? Relax.

377
00:28:05,974 --> 00:28:09,185
It's all right.
I'll just take a lock from the back here.

378
00:28:10,687 --> 00:28:13,147
You're okay. You're okay.

379
00:28:22,866 --> 00:28:24,534
You're a good son.

380
00:28:42,845 --> 00:28:44,595
Have you eaten anything?

381
00:28:48,183 --> 00:28:50,226
Somebody has to stay here for him.

382
00:28:50,310 --> 00:28:52,311
I'll stay with him tonight.

383
00:29:33,770 --> 00:29:36,022
So what's the point
of this gathering?

384
00:29:37,149 --> 00:29:39,484
We don't have to go if you don't want to.

385
00:29:39,735 --> 00:29:43,029
Most of these women were against suffrage
in the first place.

386
00:29:43,113 --> 00:29:45,323
Not too big on immigrants either.

387
00:29:45,824 --> 00:29:48,117
How did their own ancestors get here?

388
00:29:48,368 --> 00:29:50,036
The Daughters of the American Revolution?

389
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:52,663
Why, they grew in the ground like pumpkins

390
00:29:52,956 --> 00:29:56,083
and marched off with Washington
to Valley Forge.

391
00:29:58,253 --> 00:30:00,254
I'll do what's required of me.

392
00:30:02,007 --> 00:30:03,716
Not really the right answer.

393
00:30:05,177 --> 00:30:06,761
What answer would you prefer?

394
00:30:09,932 --> 00:30:11,432
What you saw...

395
00:30:14,561 --> 00:30:17,438
What you thought you saw
in my office yesterday

396
00:30:17,523 --> 00:30:19,023
couldn't have been more innocent.

397
00:30:20,984 --> 00:30:22,985
Annabelle is far from innocent.

398
00:30:23,445 --> 00:30:25,738
And I daresay
you've some experience yourself.

399
00:30:25,822 --> 00:30:28,032
We had a relationship years ago.

400
00:30:29,076 --> 00:30:30,701
It meant nothing.

401
00:30:30,786 --> 00:30:32,620
I was helping her, Margaret. That's all.

402
00:30:33,247 --> 00:30:34,664
The way you helped me?

403
00:30:34,831 --> 00:30:36,457
I thought she was your friend.

404
00:30:38,835 --> 00:30:40,294
So you wouldn't fuck her?

405
00:30:42,130 --> 00:30:44,257
That language does not become you.

406
00:30:44,466 --> 00:30:45,508
Yes.

407
00:30:46,051 --> 00:30:49,345
- You'd rather I be demure.
- I'd rather you be rational.

408
00:30:49,805 --> 00:30:50,805
Meaning what?

409
00:30:50,973 --> 00:30:54,559
That I say nothing about what I see,
what I hear?

410
00:30:55,435 --> 00:30:57,186
What have you heard?

411
00:30:58,981 --> 00:31:00,606
That you are capable of anything.

412
00:31:01,567 --> 00:31:02,817
And who told you that?

413
00:31:03,068 --> 00:31:04,652
Agent Van Alden,

414
00:31:05,487 --> 00:31:07,196
while you were out campaigning.

415
00:31:07,281 --> 00:31:10,908
Well, if you didn't tell me about it,
it couldn't have been very upsetting.

416
00:31:12,369 --> 00:31:14,203
It made me sick to my stomach.

417
00:31:15,330 --> 00:31:17,331
This whole arrangement does.

418
00:31:17,541 --> 00:31:18,666
What arrangement?

419
00:31:19,918 --> 00:31:23,129
That I'm to accept what you tell me
and ask nothing more.

420
00:31:23,213 --> 00:31:25,631
That I aid you in the business you conduct

421
00:31:25,716 --> 00:31:28,551
and pretend I don't know
what that business is.

422
00:31:28,635 --> 00:31:32,221
I don't recall you ever saying no
to anything I put in front of you.

423
00:31:32,556 --> 00:31:34,098
You make a little noise every now and then

424
00:31:34,182 --> 00:31:36,517
to remind me what a good person you are.

425
00:31:37,311 --> 00:31:39,478
But a good person
wouldn't be here right now.

426
00:31:40,564 --> 00:31:42,106
You don't know what I am.

427
00:31:42,691 --> 00:31:43,941
I don't?

428
00:31:51,992 --> 00:31:53,743
This is what you do.

429
00:31:53,994 --> 00:31:58,289
After you lie down with me, you go in there,
wash your body with this poison,

430
00:31:58,373 --> 00:31:59,373
like any whore.

431
00:32:00,042 --> 00:32:01,792
I won't have another child.

432
00:32:03,211 --> 00:32:04,545
- By me?
- By any man.

433
00:32:04,713 --> 00:32:06,213
That's not your right to decide.

434
00:32:06,298 --> 00:32:08,633
Why should you care? We're not married.

435
00:32:09,217 --> 00:32:13,262
Do you expect that I would give you,
what, an heir?

436
00:32:13,555 --> 00:32:14,972
Is that what you want me for?

437
00:32:15,057 --> 00:32:16,349
I thought you needed saving.

438
00:32:16,433 --> 00:32:18,017
And that's why you chose my husband.

439
00:32:18,644 --> 00:32:19,644
What are you talking about?

440
00:32:19,728 --> 00:32:22,605
You knew nothing of him until I came to you.

441
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:26,400
What purpose did it serve
to make me a widow?

442
00:32:26,568 --> 00:32:27,777
You need to be careful now.

443
00:32:28,236 --> 00:32:30,488
- Are you threatening me?
- I'm advising you.

444
00:32:30,572 --> 00:32:32,323
Whatever idea you've gotten into your head...

445
00:32:32,407 --> 00:32:34,784
Your brother came to me with money.

446
00:32:34,868 --> 00:32:37,161
- To help you.
- To keep me quiet.

447
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:40,081
Well, you have been, haven't you?

448
00:32:40,248 --> 00:32:43,209
Not a word about this man who beat you,

449
00:32:43,794 --> 00:32:45,961
who murdered the baby you were carrying,

450
00:32:46,505 --> 00:32:48,756
who you loved so very much.

451
00:32:49,257 --> 00:32:52,343
I have not lost one second of sleep
over what was done,

452
00:32:52,427 --> 00:32:53,636
and neither have you.

453
00:33:00,018 --> 00:33:02,770
You won't be needing that anymore, will you?

454
00:33:07,442 --> 00:33:08,609
Sir.

455
00:33:09,361 --> 00:33:11,737
- Yes?
- Sir, you got a visitor.

456
00:33:12,614 --> 00:33:13,948
Thank you.

457
00:33:20,414 --> 00:33:21,497
How is your father?

458
00:33:21,957 --> 00:33:23,791
He's on his way out.

459
00:33:24,167 --> 00:33:26,335
Mmm. I'm sorry.

460
00:33:26,628 --> 00:33:27,628
Honestly,

461
00:33:28,922 --> 00:33:30,631
I don't even know what I'm doing here.

462
00:33:31,049 --> 00:33:32,967
You're here for your mother.

463
00:33:33,552 --> 00:33:35,177
- It's your duty.
- Yeah.

464
00:33:36,638 --> 00:33:38,472
Chalky, Mr. White,

465
00:33:39,307 --> 00:33:41,726
heard back from his man in Philadelphia.

466
00:33:42,018 --> 00:33:43,060
Any sign of them?

467
00:33:43,145 --> 00:33:45,646
Mrs. D'Alessio, the mother, is there,

468
00:33:46,481 --> 00:33:49,150
the sisters and another brother.

469
00:33:49,985 --> 00:33:50,985
Which one?

470
00:33:51,153 --> 00:33:52,194
Adrian.

471
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:53,446
Never heard of him.

472
00:33:53,530 --> 00:33:54,572
He's a dentist.

473
00:33:58,326 --> 00:34:00,202
- I could go there.
- Where?

474
00:34:00,537 --> 00:34:01,662
To Philadelphia.

475
00:34:01,997 --> 00:34:04,832
What good is that?
They're lying low somewhere else.

476
00:34:06,752 --> 00:34:08,169
I would kill the mother.

477
00:34:10,547 --> 00:34:11,630
The sisters.

478
00:34:12,507 --> 00:34:14,091
And the dentist.

479
00:34:15,427 --> 00:34:17,928
That would make them stick their heads up.

480
00:34:21,099 --> 00:34:22,516
Did you run your tests?

481
00:34:23,018 --> 00:34:24,059
Yes.

482
00:34:26,146 --> 00:34:28,230
I have some information.

483
00:34:28,899 --> 00:34:31,400
We'll talk that over later, Richard.

484
00:34:39,534 --> 00:34:40,785
We need to speak frankly.

485
00:34:41,203 --> 00:34:42,328
Okay.

486
00:34:42,746 --> 00:34:43,954
Are you the next of kin?

487
00:34:44,748 --> 00:34:47,541
I'm pretty sure I'm not in the will,
if that's what you mean.

488
00:34:47,876 --> 00:34:49,627
Who else stands to gain
from your father's death?

489
00:34:50,504 --> 00:34:51,962
What are you talking about?

490
00:34:52,506 --> 00:34:53,964
The tests are pretty crude,

491
00:34:54,466 --> 00:34:57,426
but there's enough arsenic in his body
to take down a hippo.

492
00:35:00,055 --> 00:35:01,639
I don't want to.

493
00:35:02,390 --> 00:35:03,891
Yes, you do. You said so.

494
00:35:05,310 --> 00:35:06,811
We're going sailing, remember?

495
00:35:07,103 --> 00:35:08,813
You, me, Aunt Mary,

496
00:35:09,689 --> 00:35:11,565
over the ocean to Paris.

497
00:35:11,858 --> 00:35:12,983
Is Daddy coming?

498
00:35:14,361 --> 00:35:15,402
No.

499
00:35:15,570 --> 00:35:16,821
How come?

500
00:35:18,490 --> 00:35:21,700
Daddy's already been there,
and he didn't like it.

501
00:35:23,245 --> 00:35:24,453
Come on, hurry.

502
00:35:26,873 --> 00:35:28,666
Aunt Mary is waiting.

503
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:31,085
Can Gillian come?

504
00:35:35,090 --> 00:35:37,508
No. She doesn't like Paris, either.

505
00:35:49,271 --> 00:35:51,689
Come on. Let's go meet Aunt Mary.

506
00:36:19,593 --> 00:36:20,676
What's he do all day?

507
00:36:21,136 --> 00:36:23,345
Sits there. He's upset about the house.

508
00:36:23,847 --> 00:36:26,265
It's a miracle it didn't happen sooner.

509
00:36:29,853 --> 00:36:31,520
The place was a firetrap.

510
00:36:35,650 --> 00:36:37,276
So, your lady friend.

511
00:36:39,321 --> 00:36:40,654
Tell me about this row.

512
00:36:41,323 --> 00:36:42,448
It got very ugly.

513
00:36:43,408 --> 00:36:45,409
I fight with June all the time.

514
00:36:45,493 --> 00:36:48,454
We go out to the shed
to make sure the kids don't hear.

515
00:36:48,997 --> 00:36:51,498
The mouth on her... You'd be surprised.

516
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:53,250
She knows, Eli.

517
00:36:53,501 --> 00:36:55,461
She suspects, you mean.

518
00:36:56,129 --> 00:36:57,838
How could she know?

519
00:37:06,514 --> 00:37:07,514
You didn't tell her?

520
00:37:08,308 --> 00:37:09,558
I didn't deny it either.

521
00:37:09,768 --> 00:37:10,851
What the fuck were you thinking?

522
00:37:12,854 --> 00:37:13,979
That I wanted to hurt her.

523
00:37:14,397 --> 00:37:15,522
What do you think these are for?

524
00:37:16,066 --> 00:37:17,107
That's not who I am.

525
00:37:17,192 --> 00:37:18,442
It isn't?

526
00:37:19,235 --> 00:37:20,527
Who told me to get rid of her husband?

527
00:37:21,196 --> 00:37:22,321
He deserved it.

528
00:37:22,405 --> 00:37:23,530
Deserved?

529
00:37:24,366 --> 00:37:25,407
Who the fuck are you?

530
00:37:26,368 --> 00:37:28,202
Leave that shit to God
and look after business.

531
00:37:28,578 --> 00:37:30,079
